OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782442073
OL,3,CHeatwaves expose the UK's need to
OL,4,Cfuture-proof its infrastructure
OL,6,FITV News Science Correspondent Martin
OL,7,FStew has been hearing more about what
OL,8,Fwe might need to do to future-proof
OL,9,Fagainst heatwaves, in the years and
OL,10,Fdecades to come.
OL,12,FWords by Rhiannon Hopley, ITV News
OL,13,FSenior Science Producer
OL,15,FThe UK's decades-old temperature
OL,16,Frecord for June has been broken
OL,17,Fmultiple times in the space of two
OL,18,Fdays, with some parts of the country
OL,19,Fseeing highs of 36.4 degrees within a
OL,20,Fweek of the summer solstice.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782442073
OL,3,CHeatwaves expose the UK's need to
OL,4,Cfuture-proof its infrastructure
OL,6,FScientists at Reading University have
OL,7,Fattributed this heatwave to climate
OL,8,Fchange, saying that the unusually high
OL,9,Ftemperatures are 'unequivocally'
OL,10,Flinked to emissions.
OL,12,FWhile the summer of 1976 lives
OL,13,Fstrongly in the collective British
OL,14,Fmemory, it seems it will no longer be
OL,15,Fthe unusual outlier it once was.
OL,17,FAs our climate warms, scientists say
OL,18,Fhigh temperatures will become the norm.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782442073
OL,3,CHeatwaves expose the UK's need to
OL,4,Cfuture-proof its infrastructure
OL,6,FAnother study from the Met Office and
OL,7,FUniversity of Reading predicts that by
OL,8,F2056, nine-day-long heatwaves of
OL,9,Ftemperatures reaching 40 degrees are
OL,10,Fpossible.
OL,12,FEven now, the high temperatures are
OL,13,Fcausing issues. Over the last stretch
OL,14,Fof warm days, trains have been
OL,15,Fcancelled, schools have closed,
OL,16,Fseveral NHS Trusts have declared
OL,17,Fcritical incidents, and a hosepipe ban
OL,18,Fhas been introduced in Kent.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782442073
OL,3,CHeatwaves expose the UK's need to
OL,4,Cfuture-proof its infrastructure
OL,6,FThe UK is not set up to deal with
OL,7,Ftemperatures this high. In fact, much
OL,8,Fof our infrastructure was built in the
OL,9,FVictorian times when the average
OL,10,Fclimate was cooler and it is
OL,11,Fstruggling to cope in the new heat.
OL,13,FAs the mercury rises, so does demand
OL,14,Ffor water as people attempt to cool
OL,15,Fdown.
OL,17,FAnglian Water say that during the hot
OL,18,Fweather in May, the usage of water
OL,19,Fjumped from 120 litres per person per
OL,20,Fday to 152.9 litres.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782442073
OL,3,CHeatwaves expose the UK's need to
OL,4,Cfuture-proof its infrastructure
OL,6,F"Into the future, if this is the kind
OL,7,Fof typical summer that we have, we may
OL,8,Fneed to think about hosepipe bans and
OL,9,Fit may also mean things like variable
OL,10,Ftariffs where water costs more at
OL,11,Fdifferent times of year," said Geoff
OL,12,FDarch who is the Water Resources
OL,13,FStrategy Manager at Anglian Water.
OL,15,FDespite the wet winter, the hot
OL,16,Fweather and rising demand are
OL,17,Fstraining water resources.
OL,19,FAlready, South East Water has placed
OL,20,Fresidents in Kent under a hosepipe ban.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@YO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
