PN,31206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782442073
OL,3,CHeatwaves expose the UK's need to
OL,4,Cfuture-proof its infrastructure
OL,6,FHundreds of schools across the country
OL,7,Fhave closed due to the heat this week.
OL,8,FMany school buildings are either
OL,9,Funinsulated Victorian structures or
OL,10,Fpoorly insulated 1960s and 70s
OL,11,Fbuilding which are unable to cope in
OL,12,Fhigh temperatures.
OL,14,FThe National Education Union (NEU) has
OL,15,Fwritten to the education secretary to
OL,16,Fdemand funding to adapt schools to the
OL,17,Fnew climate.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782442073
OL,3,CHeatwaves expose the UK's need to
OL,4,Cfuture-proof its infrastructure
OL,6,F"Much more needs to be done to help
OL,7,Fbetter prepare our education system
OL,8,Ffor the climate emergency," the NEU
OL,9,Fsaid.
OL,11,F"Greater investment is needed to make
OL,12,Fall schools resilient to this type of
OL,13,Fextreme weather, which is only going
OL,14,Fto become more common."
OL,16,FSeveral NHS hospitals declared
OL,17,Fcritical incidents during the hot
OL,18,Fweather. In some cases, machines like
OL,19,FMRIs have overheated.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782442073
OL,3,CHeatwaves expose the UK's need to
OL,4,Cfuture-proof its infrastructure
OL,6,FIt is difficult for hospitals to use
OL,7,Fcertain types of fans and other
OL,8,Fcooling systems due to infection
OL,9,Fcontrol.
OL,11,FHot weather also means a rise in
OL,12,Fpatients. A&Es experienced their
OL,13,Fbusiest month on record in May during
OL,14,Fthe last heatwave and admissions have
OL,15,Frisen again this time.
OL,17,FThe NHS Alliance said staff are doing
OL,18,Feverything they can to ensure patients
OL,19,Fget the care they need but called for
OL,20,Fmore financial support to update
OL,21,Fhospitals for the new climate.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782442073
OL,3,CHeatwaves expose the UK's need to
OL,4,Cfuture-proof its infrastructure
OL,6,F"There is a lesson as these hot spells
OL,7,Fbecome more frequent" it said.
OL,9,FDuring the heat, demand for power can
OL,10,Fgo up as people use fans and aircon.
OL,11,FEquipment like fridges can also become
OL,12,Fless efficient.
OL,14,FIt also affects power generation.
OL,15,FNuclear power plants use water to cool
OL,16,Fdown but when the weather gets too
OL,17,Fhot, this interferes with water
OL,18,Ftemperature. In France, EDF has shut
OL,19,Fdown two of its nuclear power stations
OL,20,Ffor this reason.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782442073
OL,3,CHeatwaves expose the UK's need to
OL,4,Cfuture-proof its infrastructure
OL,6,FThe heat dome covering the UK also
OL,7,Fmeans there is much less wind than
OL,8,Fusual affecting the amount of wind
OL,9,Fpower it is possible to generate.
OL,11,FYesterday, NESO who look after the
OL,12,FNational Grid put out an Electricity
OL,13,FMargin Notice which asks the market
OL,14,Ffor any additional power they can
OL,15,Fgive. It has never been issued before
OL,16,Fin the summer. It was later retracted.
OL,18,FOn the rails, hot weather causes
OL,19,Foverhead lines which power trains to
OL,20,Fsag. Trains have to travel more slowly
OL,21,Fto avoid damaging them.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782442073
OL,3,CHeatwaves expose the UK's need to
OL,4,Cfuture-proof its infrastructure
OL,6,FThe rails themselves can also expand
OL,7,Fin the heat becoming up to 20 degrees
OL,8,Fhotter than the air around them and
OL,9,Fcan cause them to buckle.
OL,11,F"Really hot weather puts huge amounts
OL,12,Fof energy into steel rails, steels
OL,13,Fwires, our telecoms and signaling
OL,14,Fequipment," said Jake Kelly, Deputy
OL,15,FChief Executive of Network Rail.
OL,17,F"Ultimately, the Victorian
OL,18,Finfrastructure that we have inherited
OL,19,Fwasn't designed for the kind of really
OL,20,Fextreme heat that we are seeing today"
OL,26,@|D@fO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31212
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782442073
OL,3,CHeatwaves expose the UK's need to
OL,4,Cfuture-proof its infrastructure
OL,6,FWhen temperatures hit 30C, the roads
OL,7,Fthemselves can become even hotter,
OL,8,Foften reaching temperatures of above
OL,9,F50C. This can lead them to start
OL,10,Fmelting as excess tar or liquid
OL,11,Fbitumen rises to the surface.
OL,13,FA number of councils had gritters on
OL,14,Fstandby for this reason. Unlike in the
OL,15,Fwinter when they spread salt, hot
OL,16,Fweather gritters spread granite dust
OL,17,Fto absorb the soft bitumen and make
OL,18,Fthe road surface less sticky.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31213
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782442073
OL,3,CHeatwaves expose the UK's need to
OL,4,Cfuture-proof its infrastructure
OL,6,FIn the House of Commons on Wednesday,
OL,7,FMPs argued over funding for new Net
OL,8,FZero plans and how to cut emissions.
OL,10,F"If anyone in this chamber still
OL,11,Fthinks climate change is a problem for
OL,12,Ftomorrow, they should step outside
OL,13,Ftoday," said the UK's Climate Minister
OL,14,FKatie White MP.
OL,16,F"Today's debate is not taking place
OL,17,Fagainst the backdrop of climate
OL,18,Fchange, it's taking place in the
OL,19,Fmiddle of it."
OL,26,@rD@AOUuD@GO]xD@AOU{D@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31214
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782442073
OL,3,CHeatwaves expose the UK's need to
OL,4,Cfuture-proof its infrastructure
OL,6,FBut Conservative and Reform MPs raised
OL,7,Fconcerns about the costs of pursuing
OL,8,FNet Zero.
OL,10,F"I care about the consumer, I care
OL,11,Fabout jobs, I care about food and I
OL,12,Fcare about the price of energy," said
OL,13,FShadow Secretary of State for Energy
OL,14,FSecurity and Net Zero Claire Coutinho,
OL,15,Fas she argued that the transition
OL,16,Fplans are unsustainable.
OL,26,@rD@AOUtD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
